<TITLE> Ershad, Badruddoza condole </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)Politicians, including former presidents Hussein Muhammad Ershad and AQM Badruddoza Chowdhury, condoled the death of Dr MA Wazed Miah, nuclear physicist and prime minister Sheikh Hasina's husband. They sympathised with the bereaved family over the death of Dr Miah, 66, who died on Saturday after prolonged illness at the Square Hospital. Liberal Democratic Party chairman Oli Ahmed, BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain, former BNP secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan, former information minister and BNP leader M Shamsul Islam, Dhaka mayor Sadeque Hossain Khoka, former mayor Abul Hasnat, BNP MP Salahudin Quader Chowdhury, among others, in messages mourned the death. Bangladesh Muktijuddha Projanma, Dhaka Journalists' Union, Awami Sangskritik Forum, Bangladesh Chhatra League, BGMEA, Bangladesh Volleyball Federation, Bangabandhu Juba Parisad, National People's Party, Bangladesh Police Service Association and Dhaka Metropolitan Police were among many other organisations to join the mourning
